occurrenceRemarks: The first picture is super blurry (sorry) but it is of a small fish about an inch long. There are a whole bunch of these little guppies in this hidden pond area. They look very much like mosquito fish but have vibrant red tails and some also have yellow fins. The largest one I’ve seen was about 2 or 2-and-a-half inches long. Thank you so much for letting me know the name! I’ve updated the title! (13-2-23) (*Please note I did not harm any of these fish in the last three photos! These were ones I’d had from a while ago and pick one up to show the colors. These lil guys were gently put back into the water quickly afterwards and they peacefully swam away fine.)
